From: Lawrence Manning <>
Subject: Spurious mouse movements (2.2.13)
Sender: linux-kernel-owner@vger.kernel.org
Precedence: bulk
List-ID: <linux-kernel.vger.kernel.org>
X-Mailing-List: linux-kernel@vger.kernel.org
X-Lkml-Link: https://lkml.org/lkml/1999/12/7/120

Linux version 2.2.13 (root@aslak.demon.co.uk) (gcc version 2.7.2.3) #2 Wed
Oct 20 22:44:01 BST 1999
I've noticed before that sometimes my screensaver wakes up when the mouse
dosn't appear to have moved.  I put it down to the mouse moving due to
"air turbulance" etc or some noise on the cable except for just now when
the mouse zoomed across the entire screen from around the center to the
right edge at a fairly fast pace.  Im on PPP here, IDE system.  At the
time there was virtually no load, but the modem was dialed so odd packets
could have been coming in.  It's a PS/2 M$ InteleMouse with the wheel.
When the pointer had reached the edge of the screen, everything was
normal.  No crashes, no keyboard problems, no modem problems.
My kernel config and list of loaded modules is at the bottom.  I have
XFree86 3.3.5 here. I dont run gpm so I cant tell you if the problem
happens there too. :-(
If you want any other information, please ask!
Lawrence
